               <msContents>
                  <summary>An abridged version of <title>Qānūn al-Nisā’</title> (Rules for Women) by Jamāl al-Dīn Khvānsārī (d. 1713), a popular satire of prevailing superstitions in late Safavid-era Iran. Written the style of a legal manual, it features the rulings of five female religious scholars, chiefly one named <hi rend="italic">Kuls̱ūm Nanah</hi>, hence an popular alternative title for the work. 
                     </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_338-item1">
                     <author ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/200330643/" key="person_200330643" change="#ids-cleanup">
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="standard" role="abr">Anonymous</persName>
                     </author>
                     <author ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/117158606" key="person_117158606"><persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="standard" role="ant att">Jamāl al-Dīn Khvānsarī</persName></author>
                     <editor role="scr"><persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f6907" role="scr">Aṣālat ʿAlī Bahārī<foreign xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">اصالتعلی بهاری</foreign></persName></editor>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_7280">Qānūn al-Nisā’</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_7280">قانون النساء</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_7280">‘Aqā'id al-Nisā’</title>
                     <title type="alt" xml:lang="fa" key="work_7280">عقائد النساء</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_7280">Kuls̱ūm Nanah</title>
                     <title type="alt" xml:lang="fa" key="work_7280">کلثوم ننه</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_7280">ʻAqāʼid al-Nisvān</title>
                     <title type="alt" xml:lang="fa" key="work_7280">عقائد النسوان</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa" type="beginning"><locus from="1b" to="1b"> برگ ۱پ (folio 1b):</locus>
                        اما بعد این رسالۀ است در باب آداب واطوار زنان</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa"><locus from="53a" to="53a"> برگ ۵۳ر (folio 53a):</locus>
                     و وجه او را بمصرف مشروع میرسانند
                     </explicit>
                     <colophon xml:lang="fa"><locus from="53a" to="53a"> برگ ۵۳ر (folio 53a):</locus>
                        تمام شد کتاب قانون النساء خط خام اصالتعلی
                        بهاری</colophon>
                     <colophon>Undated but signed by the scribe <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f6907" role="scr">Aṣālat ʿAlī Bahārī</persName>.</colophon>
                     <note>While the opening denotes all fifteen chapter headings found in the original work, this volume only contains fourteen given in variant order, but omits one on <hi rend="italic">naẕrī</hi> dishes offered by women to the poor during the month of Muharram. This redaction also varies from <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_4624">Bodleian MS Ouseley 15, no 2</ref>. British orientalist James A. Atkinson (1780–1852) published a loose translation of excerpted chapters in London in <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1832">1832</date>.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_338-item1-item1">
                        <locus from="1b" to="2a">Folios 1b–2a.</locus>
                        <title xml:lang="en">Introduction</title>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_338-item1-item2">
                        <locus from="2a" to="2b">Folios 2a–2b.</locus>
                        <title xml:lang="en">Table of Contents</title>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_338-item1-item3">
                        <locus from="2b" to="8b">Folios 2b–8b.</locus>
                        <title xml:lang="en">Chapter 1: On what is absolutely required of women deficient in intellect and faith.</title>
                        <title xml:lang="fa">در آنجه عمل کردن در مذهب این طائفه ناقص العقل ناقص الدین واجب مطلق است.</title>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_338-item1-item4">
                        <locus from="8b" to="12a">Folios 8b–12a.</locus>
                        <title xml:lang="en">Chapter 2: On what prior ‘ulamā' regarded as authentic traditions.</title>
                        <title xml:lang="fa">در آنچه علمای سبق سنت مؤکد دانسته‌اند و تصریح باستحباب آن نموده‌اند.</title>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_338-item1-item5">
                        <locus from="12a" to="13b">Folios 12a–13b.</locus>
                        <title xml:lang="en">On what bestows fortune upon daughters according to several sources. </title>
                        <title xml:lang="fa">در بیان کشادن بخت دختران چندین قسم نقل شده است. </title>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_338-item1-item6">
                        <locus from="13b" to="16b">Folios 13b–16b.</locus>
                        <title xml:lang="en">On prayer and fasting and its forms. </title>
                        <title xml:lang="fa">در بیان نماز و روزه مخترعی ایشان. </title>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_338-item1-item7">
                        <locus from="16b" to="21b">16b–21b.</locus>
                        <title xml:lang="en">On obligatory fasting and its times. </title>
                        <title xml:lang="fa">در بیان روزه‌های واجب و سنت ایشان و آداب آنها. </title>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_338-item1-item8">
                        <locus from="21b" to="25b">21b–25b.</locus>
                        <title xml:lang="en">On wedding nights and the practices of brides and what pertains to it. </title>
                        <title xml:lang="fa">در آداب شب زنان و آنجه برو متعلق است. </title>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_338-item1-item9">
                        <locus from="25b" to="30a">25b–30a.</locus>
                        <title xml:lang="en">On pregnancy. </title>
                        <title xml:lang="fa">در بیان زائدن زنان و وقت حامله بودن. </title>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_338-item1-item10">
                        <locus from="30a" to="32a">30a–32a.</locus>
                        <title xml:lang="en">On the rules for women attending the bath house. </title>
                        <title xml:lang="fa">در بیان احکام حمام رفتن زنان. </title>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_338-item1-item11">
                        <locus from="32a" to="35a">32a–35a</locus>
                        <title xml:lang="en">On singing and playing various instruments.</title>
                        <title xml:lang="fa">سرودها و سازها و اوقات شنیدن اینها. </title>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_338-item1-item12">
                        <locus from="35a" to="40a">35a–40a.</locus>
                        <title xml:lang="en">On the interaction of women, their husbands, and their husbands’ families.</title>
                        <title xml:lang="fa">در بیان سلوک زن با شوهر واقوام شوهر و سلوک شوهر با زن. </title>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_338-item1-item13">
                        <locus from="40a" to="42a">40a–42a.</locus>
                        <title xml:lang="en">On devices that women employ to deter the evil eye.</title>
                        <title xml:lang="fa">در بیان تعویزاتی که از برای چشم زخم مخترع این طائفه شده. </title>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_338-item1-item14">
                        <locus from="42a" to="42a">42a–42a.</locus>
                        <title xml:lang="en">On intimates and strangers.</title>
                        <title xml:lang="fa">در بیان محرم و نمحرم. </title>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_338-item1-item15">
                        <locus from="42a" to="48a">42a–48a.</locus>
                        <title xml:lang="en">On welcoming and saying goodbye to guests.</title>
                        <title xml:lang="fa"> در بیان وقت آمدن مهمان یا وقت بیرون رفتن او. </title>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_338-item1-item16">
                        <locus from="48a" to="53a">48a–53a.</locus>
                        <title xml:lang="en">Conclusion: ‘On some miscellaneous topics’.</title>
                        <title xml:lang="fa">خاتمه در باب متفرقات. </title>
                     </msItem>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
